];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<CommercialHero
  title="Ice-O-Matic Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle={`ICE Series cube + Pearl Ice nugget + EF flake. Full Ice-O-Matic service across LA, OC, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Ali Group parts network. ${phone}`}
  heroImageTitle="Ice-O-Matic Repair"
/>

<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Ice-O-Matic service</p>
    <h2>Ice-O-Matic: mid-tier value within the Ali Group ice machine portfolio.</h2>

    <p>Ice-O-Matic is the mid-tier value brand within Ali Group's commercial ice machine lineup. Sister brand to Scotsman, which sits in Ali Group's mid-premium tier. US heritage since 1953, US operations in Denver Colorado, Italian parent corporation Ali Group based in Milan. Acquired by Ali Group around 2002. Long Ali Group integration means component sharing with Scotsman in some areas.</p>

    <p>Important context: Ice-O-Matic and Scotsman are not the same machine. Different product lineups, different price tiers, different feature sets. But they're sister brands within Ali Group sharing some architectural similarities (horizontal evaporator plus spray pump architecture both brands use, common component compatibility on some service items). Ali Group efficiency means parts logistics work across both brands.</p>

    <p>Our techs service Ice-O-Matic across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. <strong>ICE Series cube ice machines</strong> (flagship): ICE0250 (250 lb/day), ICE0320 (320 lb/day), ICE0500 (500 lb/day), ICE0606 (600 lb/day), ICE0806 (800 lb/day), ICE1006 (1,000 lb/day), ICE1407 (1,400 lb/day large modular). <strong>Pearl Ice nugget</strong>: GEMU090, GEMU450 (Ali Group's nugget answer at mid-tier price). <strong>EF Series flake</strong> (less common than Hoshizaki F-Series, but available).</p>

    <p>EPA 608 Universal plus <strong>R-290 certification</strong> for the post-2020 Ice-O-Matic transition to propane refrigerant on newer ICE models. BHGS #A49573. BBB Accredited. Phones answered 24/7. Parent context: <a href="/commercial/ice-machines/">commercial ice machine repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 LINEUP & WHAT FAILS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Lineup and what fails</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Ice-O-Matic series and common service items.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Ice-O-Matic uses the ICE prefix on cube ice machines, GEMU on Pearl Ice nugget, EF on flake. Variants: A (air-cooled), W (water-cooled), R (remote-condensed). We identify by serial number first.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">ICE Series Cube Ice Machines</h3>
    <p>ICE0250 (250 lb/day small modular), ICE0320 (320 lb/day undercounter or modular, the most popular Ice-O-Matic small machine), ICE0500/ICE0500HA (500 lb/day), ICE0606 (600 lb/day), ICE0806 (800 lb/day), ICE1006 (1,000 lb/day), ICE1407 (1,400 lb/day large). Common in budget restaurants, cafés, mid-tier hospitality.</p>

    <p><strong>Same horizontal evaporator plus spray pump architecture as Scotsman.</strong> Water sprayed up onto the evaporator from a sump below. The spray pump is an additional service item beyond what cell-and-curtain Hoshizaki or vertical-evaporator Manitowoc machines have.</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 5 to 8:</strong> Spray pump wear, slightly faster than Scotsman due to value-tier component cost optimization. $360 to $520.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 4 to 7:</strong> Water inlet valve. $260 to $420.</li>
      <li><strong>Ongoing:</strong> Cleaning service required. Same scale issues across all brands. Skipping cleaning destroys evaporators 3 to 5 years in.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5 to 9:</strong> Hot gas valve and harvest cycle issues.</li>
      <li><strong>Newer models:</strong> Smart Connect IoT diagnostic platform. Read codes correctly first.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8+:</strong> AgION antimicrobial coating wear. Cleaning becomes more critical on aged machines.</li>
      <li><strong>Periodic:</strong> AlpineAir filter replacement, Ice-O-Matic-specific filtration system.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8 to 12:</strong> Compressor mechanical wear. Value-tier service life replace-vs-repair threshold.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Pearl Ice Nugget Series (GEMU090, GEMU450)</h3>
    <p>Ali Group's mid-tier nugget answer (parallel to sister Scotsman Brilliance). GEMU090 smaller, GEMU450 larger. Auger-driven inside an evaporator drum, compressed and extruded into nugget shape before discharge.</p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 5 to 8:</strong> Auger gear reducer wear, slightly faster than Scotsman Brilliance.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 6 to 9:</strong> Extrusion mechanism wear.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 7 to 11:</strong> Auger motor.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="series-h3">EF Series Flake Ice</h3>
    <p>Auger-driven flake architecture similar to Hoshizaki F-Series. Less common in the LA market but serviceable. Auger motor and gear reducer at year 6 to 9 are the typical service items, same as flake on any brand.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 TYPICAL REPAIRS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Top Ice-O-Matic repairs in our 5-county territory.</h2>

    <p>In rough order of frequency on Ice-O-Matic service calls:</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Spray pump replacement (ICE Series cube).</strong> The most common Ice-O-Matic service item. Same failure mode as sister brand Scotsman. $360 to $520.</li>
      <li><strong>Cleaning service.</strong> $200 to $340. Routine on every brand, more critical on aged Ice-O-Matic units where AgION coating has worn.</li>
      <li><strong>Water inlet valve replacement.</strong> $260 to $420.</li>
      <li><strong>AlpineAir filter replacement.</strong> Ice-O-Matic-specific filtration system. $80 to $160.</li>
      <li><strong>Hot gas valve replacement.</strong> Harvest cycle issue.</li>
      <li><strong>Smart Connect diagnostic plus targeted repair.</strong> Newer ICE models with IoT platform. Read codes correctly first.</li>
      <li><strong>Auger gear reducer (Pearl Ice nugget).</strong>  $580 to $880.</li>
      <li><strong>Refrigerant leak repair.</strong> EPA 608 leak detection, brazed repair, evacuate, recharge. R-290 systems require R-290 certification.</li>
      <li><strong>Condenser fan motor (-A air-cooled units).</strong> Coastal salt accelerates wear in Marina del Rey, Manhattan Beach, Newport Beach.</li>
      <li><strong>Compressor replacement (8 to 12 year units).</strong> Value-tier service life shorter than Scotsman premium.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five Ice-O-Matic jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pasadena, Ice-O-Matic ICE0500HA cube, 9 years old, R-404A</h3>
        <p>Coffee shop. Ice production at 60% nameplate. Diagnosed: spray pump wear (the Scotsman-architecture sister brand has the same failure mode). Replaced spray pump. Total: $120 plus $440 part plus 2 hours = $720.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Beverly Hills, Ice-O-Matic ICE0320 undercounter cube, 7 years old</h3>
        <p>Café. Water inlet fault on Smart Connect display. Replaced water inlet valve. Smart Connect platform showed diagnostic correctly, no parts swap guesswork needed. Total: $120 plus $290 part plus 1 hour = $410.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Marina del Rey, Ice-O-Matic ICE0606A air-cooled cube, 8 years old</h3>
        <p>Restaurant. Refrigerant slow leak plus scale buildup combination. EPA 608 leak detection, brazed evaporator joint repair, cleaned evaporator, recharged R-404A. Total: $120 plus $480 refrigerant plus $280 cleaning plus $620 labor = $1,500.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>West Hollywood, Ice-O-Matic Pearl Ice GEMU090 nugget, 6 years old</h3>
        <p>Bar. Auger noise, nugget production reduced. Diagnosed: gear reducer wear (typical 5 to 8 year on Pearl Ice). Replaced gear reducer. Total: $120 plus $620 part plus 2.5 hours = $980.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Calabasas, multi-unit restaurant chain, 4× Ice-O-Matic ICE0606</h3>
        <p>Coordinated through corporate facility manager. Quarterly fleet cleaning plus 2 spray pump replacements plus 1 water filter replacement. Single visit fleet service. Total: $120 plus $1,120 cleaning ($280 × 4) plus $880 spray pumps plus $160 filter = $2,280. Corporate appreciated single-dispatch fleet pricing.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scope</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What we do for Ice-O-Matic, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>ICE Series cube (ICE0250, ICE0320, ICE0500, ICE0500HA, ICE0606, ICE0806, ICE1006, ICE1407)</li>
      <li>Pearl Ice nugget (GEMU090, GEMU450)</li>
      <li>EF Series flake</li>
      <li>All variants (-A air-cooled, W water-cooled, R remote-condensed)</li>
      <li>All EPA-permitted refrigerants Ice-O-Matic uses (R-22 legacy, R-134a, R-404A, R-290 hydrocarbon: we have R-290 certification)</li>
      <li>AlpineAir filtration system service and filter replacement</li>
      <li>Smart Connect IoT diagnostic platform on newer models</li>
      <li>AgION antimicrobial coating maintenance</li>
      <li>Ali Group parts network access (sister Scotsman component compatibility on some service items)</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new Ice-O-Matic installation (Ali Group authorized installer trade); sister Ali Group brands in other equipment categories (Champion dishwashers, Carpigiani gelato are different equipment categories with their own service paths); Scotsman ice machines on this page (separate brand, separate page: see <a href="/commercial/ice-machines/brands/scotsman/">Scotsman ice machine repair</a>); Beverage-Air refrigeration on this page (sister Ali Group brand, refrigeration category: see <a href="/commercial/refrigeration/brands/beverage-air/">Beverage-Air refrigerator repair</a>).</p>

    <p>For warranty-eligible repairs, we document the failure on-site, the operator processes the claim through Ali Group North American distribution (5 to 7 day standard part ship), and we install the replacement.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 PRICING -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Ice-O-Matic repair costs.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Diagnostic is $120 (commercial tier), waived with the repair. OEM Ice-O-Matic parts via Ali Group Denver distribution. Sister Scotsman components compatible on some service items, an Ali Group efficiency advantage we use to reduce part-wait time.</p>

    <table class="price-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Repair</th><th>Typical Cost</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Diagnostic</td><td>$120, waived with repair</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Cleaning service</td><td>$200 to $340</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Water filter replacement</td><td>$80 to $180</td></tr>
        <tr><td>AlpineAir filter replacement</td><td>$80 to $160</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Spray pump replacement (ICE Series)</td><td>$360 to $520</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Water inlet valve</td><td>$260 to $420</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hot gas valve</td><td>$340 to $540</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Harvest sensor</td><td>$200 to $340</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Smart Connect board diagnostic</td><td>$200 to $280</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Auger gear reducer (Pearl Ice)</td><td>$580 to $880</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Extrusion mechanism (Pearl Ice)</td><td>$480 to $780</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor (-A)</td><td>$300 to $520</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Refrigerant leak repair plus recharge</td><td>$700 to $1,400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor replacement (ICE0250 to ICE0606)</td><td>$1,400 to $2,000</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Compressor replacement (ICE0806 to ICE1407)</td><td>$1,800 to $2,600</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Multi-component repair</td><td>$1,000 to $2,400</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Warranty</td><td>90 days parts and labor</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>Honest opinion on this tier: a 10+ year-old ICE Series with major compressor failure is usually a replace conversation. Value-tier service life is 8 to 12 years. New ICE0606 landed runs roughly $3,800 to $4,600 commercial wholesale. A $2,000 compressor swap on a unit with worn spray pump, faded AgION coating, and aged water inlet valve you'll be replacing within 18 months anyway is not the right call. We say so on the diagnostic.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 07 WHY US -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Why us for Ice-O-Matic</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What separates our Ice-O-Matic service from general ice machine repair.</h2>

    <ul class="reasons-list">
      <li><strong>Sister brand expertise across Ali Group.</strong> We service Scotsman, Ice-O-Matic, and Beverage-Air refrigeration (all Ali Group). Component compatibility knowledge across sister brands reduces part-wait time.</li>
      <li><strong>Spray pump architecture.</strong> Same horizontal evaporator plus spray pump as Scotsman. Specific service knowledge applies to both. Different from Hoshizaki cell-and-curtain or Manitowoc vertical evaporator.</li>
      <li><strong>EPA 608 Universal plus R-290 certification.</strong> Required for post-2020 Ice-O-Matic models on hydrocarbon refrigerant. See our <a href="/credentials/epa-certified/">EPA 608 page</a>.</li>
      <li><strong>Smart Connect IoT diagnostic.</strong> Newer ICE models. Read codes correctly first instead of trial-and-error parts swapping.</li>
      <li><strong>AlpineAir plus AgION antimicrobial maintenance.</strong> Ice-O-Matic-specific feature management.</li>
      <li><strong>Mid-tier value tier service approach.</strong> We calibrate service to the expected 8 to 12 year life on ICE Series, not the premium-tier 12 to 15 year expectation. Different replace-vs-repair math.</li>
      <li><strong>Ali Group parts network access.</strong> Denver Ice-O-Matic distribution plus Vernon Hills Scotsman distribution plus Beverage-Air Winston-Salem distribution. Sister brand component compatibility.</li>
      <li><strong>Multi-unit chain coordination.</strong> Quarterly fleet cleaning plus repair coordinated through corporate facility managers. Single-dispatch fleet pricing.</li>
      <li><strong>24/7 phone answering, no emergency surcharge.</strong> $120 anytime.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus BBB Accredited.</strong> Verifiable. Eight branches across SoCal. Same-day in most areas, next-day RC and Temecula.</li>
      <li><strong>Honest replace-vs-repair.</strong> A 10+ year-old ICE Series with a failed compressor on this value tier may not be worth fixing. We say so on the diagnostic.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Sister sub-services: <a href="/commercial/ice-machines/cube-ice-repair/">cube ice repair</a>, <a href="/commercial/ice-machines/cleaning-service/">scheduled cleaning service</a>. Sibling brands: <a href="/commercial/ice-machines/brands/scotsman/">Scotsman</a>, <a href="/commercial/ice-machines/brands/hoshizaki/">Hoshizaki</a>, <a href="/commercial/ice-machines/brands/manitowoc/">Manitowoc</a>. Sister Ali Group refrigeration: <a href="/commercial/refrigeration/brands/beverage-air/">Beverage-Air repair</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 08 FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
